      n n        Civic Engagement n       Expand Civic Engagement menu  n n                  Registration n                  n n                  Education n                  n n                  Participation n                 Eyebrow menu Donate UIC Connection Student Affairs UIC menu UIC edu Campus Map Leadership  n      View Menu n       nDown arrow icon n n n n n n Down arrow icon Leadership Student Leadership and Civic Engagement believes that leadership is the process by which individuals facilitate positive social change  Anchored in the Social Change Model of Leadership Development  we believe that everyone can lead and create positive change at UIC and in the greater community  Our programs and workshops provide opportunities for students to explore and discover their personal style of leadership  while building skills to help them succeed in their academic and professional lives  We emphasize the connections between individuals  groups  and community  and focus on helping students link their passions to a greater cause Programs  n n n n n n            Flashpoint n         n n  n n n n n n            Ignite n         n n  n n n n n n            Catalyst n         n n  n n n n n n            Institute n         n n  n n n n n n            Awards  CSSLA  n         n n  n n n n n n            University Ambassadors n         n n  n n n n n n            Workshops n         n n Social Change Model The Social Change Model was built upon the following assumptions  The Social Change Model approaches leadership as a purposeful  collaborative  values based process that results in positive social change Source  nHigher Education Research Institute         A social change model of leadership development  Version III  Los Angeles  University of California Los Angeles Higher Education Research Institute   News Meet Marvely Camacho  Committee Leader Meet Marvely Camacho  Committee Leader Giving Back  IGNITE Mentor Marissa Scavelli Giving Back  IGNITE Mentor Marissa Scave